tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mild metabolic acidosis (low CO₂). Total protein is slightly decreased, but albumin is normal. Lipid profile reveals elevated triglycerides and LDL cholesterol, increasing cardiovascular risk. Liver enzymes and electrolytes are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and cardiovascular risk management.
